# AI/ML Internship – Day 7: LLM Fine-Tuning with LoRA & PEFT

## Overview
Day 7 focused on parameter-efficient fine-tuning of Large Language Models (LLMs) using LoRA (Low-Rank Adaptation) and the PEFT library. The session explored how to efficiently adapt pretrained Transformer models while minimizing GPU memory usage and computational cost on NVIDIA H200 GPUs.

## Topics Covered
- Introduction to Large Language Models (LLMs)
- LoRA (Low-Rank Adaptation)
- PEFT (Parameter-Efficient Fine-Tuning)
- Hugging Face Transformers
- Efficient LLM Fine-Tuning
- NVIDIA H200 GPU Acceleration

## Practical Learning
- Loaded pretrained LLMs using Hugging Face.
- Explored LoRA-based fine-tuning techniques.
- Understood PEFT workflows for efficient model adaptation.
- Learned memory-efficient training strategies on GPU infrastructure.

## Skills Gained
- LLM Fine-Tuning
- LoRA
- PEFT
- Hugging Face Transformers
- GPU Optimization
- Parameter-Efficient Training

## Tools & Libraries
- Python
- PyTorch
- Hugging Face Transformers
- PEFT
- LoRA
